[SN]TITLE[SN]
Robogami: the future of robotics?

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Scientists in Switzerland are developing a form of robot that resembles origami.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
18 November 2015 Last updated at 08:33 GMT
They hope the design will make them cheaper and more versatile.
The robots are a combination of multiple, foldable joints and the aim is to help make a more flexible form of robot.
This means that unlike other robots, "robogamis" do not need to be built with a clear function in mind.
BBC Click's Vieri Capretta spoke to Jamie Paik, the Director of the Reconfigurable Robotics Laboratory in Lausanne, Switzerland.
